## Type Validation Rule

### Rule Name: repositories-rules

### Description:
Before implementing any new endpoint or modifying existing ones, ensure proper type validation by following these steps:

1. Check if the entity type exists in `/packages/types/src/entities/`
   - If yes, ensure it follows the naming convention `IEntityNameEntity`
   - If no, create the appropriate type definition first

2. Verify corresponding body request type in `/packages/types/src/@types/body-requests/`
   - Body request types should follow the naming pattern:
     - For POST: `IPostEntityNameBodyRequest`
     - For PUT: `IPutEntityNameBodyRequest`

3. Ensure payload consistency:
   - Body request types should extend or reference the main entity type when appropriate
   - Use `Omit<>` or `Pick<>` to derive from the main entity type
   - Example:
     ```typescript
     import { IEntityNameEntity } from "../entities/entity-name.entity";
     
     export interface IPostEntityNameBodyRequest {
         // Only include fields needed for creation
         field1: string;
         field2: number;
         // Omit auto-generated fields like id, createdAt, etc.
     }
     ```

4. Verify corresponding params to get query type in `/packages/types/src/params/`
   - Params types should follow the naming pattern using EntityName and METHOD:
     - For GET All: `IGetAllEntityNameParams`
     - For GET Specific: `IGetByIdEntityNameParams`

5. Ensure params consistency:
   - Example:
     ```typescript
     import { IEntityNameEntity } from "../entities/entity-name.entity.ts";
     
     export interface IGetAllEntitiNameParams {
         // Only include fields needed for creation
         order: "name-desc" | "name-asc";
         field2: IEntityName["propriety"];
         // Omit auto-generated fields like id, createdAt, etc.p
     }
     ```

8. Verify corresponding dto type to correct types type in `/apps/backend/src/modules/module-name/dtos/entity-name.dto.ts`
   - Every dto NEEED use `Exact` helper type to ensure :
     - For GET methods search type in: `/packages/types/src/params/`
     - For PUT or POST methods search type inside: `/packages/types/src/body-requests/`

7. Check if have one contract inside `/apps/backend/src/modules/module-name/repositories/entity-name/entity-name.contract.repository.ts`
   - The contract need be one class to implement by repository
   - The contract will be injected on service to not pass database responsabilities to service 
    - Example of class ContractRepository:
    ```typescript
     import { IGetEntityNameParams } from "@global-types/params/entity-name";
     import { IGetEntityNameResponse } from "@global-types/responses/trigger";
     import { IEntityNameEntity } from "@global-types/entities/entity-name.entity.ts";
     export abstract class IEntityNameContractRepository {
        abstract findAndCount(
            filter: IGetEntityNameParams,
            sectorId: number,
        ): Promise<IGetEntityNameResponse>;

        abstract save(payload: Omit<IEntityNameEntity, "id" | "files" | "attachments" | "lastUsed">): Promise<IEntityNameEntity>;

        abstract findOne(id: number): Promise<IEntityNameEntity | null>;
     }

    ```

8. Check if have one repository inside `/apps/backend/src/modules/module-name/repositories/entity-name/entity-name.prisma.repository.ts`
   - The contract need be one class to implement by repository
   - The contract will be injected on service to not pass database responsabilities to service 
   - Every PrismaRepository have implemens Exact the contract to not pass wrong implementations
    - Example of class Prisma:
    ```typescript
        import { Injectable } from '@nestjs/common';
        import { EntityNameRepositoryContract } from './entity-name.contract.repository';
        import { IEntityNameEntity } from '@global-types/class';
        import { PrismaService } from 'src/prisma/prisma.service';
        import { GetEntityNameParams } from '@global-types/params/entity-name.params';
        import { GetEntityNameesResponse } from '@global-types/responses/entity-name.response';
        import { Prisma } from '@prisma/client';
        import { CreateEntityNameBodyRequest } from '@global-types/body-requests/entity-name.body-request';
        @Injectable()
        export class EntityNamePrismaRepository implements EntityNameRepositoryContract {
            constructor(private readonly prisma: PrismaService) { }

            async getAllEntityNamees(params: GetEntityNameParams): Promise<GetEntityNameesResponse> {
                let { page = 1, pageSize = 10, search = '' } = params;
                page = Math.max(1, page);

                const skip = (page - 1) * pageSize;
                const take = pageSize;

                const conditions: Prisma.EntityNameWhereInput[] = [];

                if (search) {
                    conditions.push({
                        OR: [
                            {
                                name: { contains: search, mode: 'insensitive' },
                            },
                            {
                                description: {
                                    contains: search,
                                    mode: 'insensitive',
                                },
                            },
                        ],
                    });
                }
                const where: Prisma.EntityNameWhereInput =
                    conditions.length > 0 ? { AND: conditions } : {};
                const classes = await this.prisma.entityName.findMany({
                    where,
                    skip,
                    take,
                    orderBy: {
                        id: 'desc',
                    },
                });

                const total = await this.prisma.entityName.count({ where });
                const lastPage = Math.ceil(total / pageSize);
                return {
                    data: classes,
                    metadata: {
                        page,
                        hasNextPage: total > page * pageSize,
                        hasPreviousPage: page > 1,
                        total,
                        lastPage,
                    },
                };
            }

            async getEntityNameById(id: number): Promise<IEntityNameEntity | null> {
                return this.prisma.entityName.findUnique({
                    where: { id },
                });
            }

            async createEntityName(classData: CreateEntityNameBodyRequest): Promise<IEntityNameEntity> {
                const {
                    name,
                    description,
                    difficulty = 'EASY_1',
                } = classData;

                return this.prisma.entityName.create({
                    data: {
                        name,
                        description,
                        difficulty,
                    },
                });
            }

            async updateEntityName(
                id: number,
                classData: Partial<IEntityNameEntity>,
            ): Promise<IEntityNameEntity> {
                return this.prisma.entityName.update({
                    where: { id },
                    data: classData,
                });
            }

            async deleteEntityName(id: number): Promise<{ success: boolean; id: number }> {
                await this.prisma.entityName.delete({
                    where: { id },
                });
                return { success: true, id };
            }
        } 

    ```
     - Example of class Elastic Search Repository:
    ```typescript
        import { Injectable } from '@nestjs/common';
        import { Client, estypes } from '@elastic/elasticsearch';
        import { Exact } from '@global-types/utils/exact';
        import { EntityNameRepositoryContract } from './entity-name.contract.repository';
        import {
        FormElement,
        IEntityName,
        } from '@global-types/entities/entity-name.entity.ts';
        import {
        GetEntityNamesParams,
        OrderEntityName,
        } from '@global-types/params/entity-names.params';
        import { GetEntityNamesResponse } from '@global-types/responses/entity-name.response';
        import { IEntityName2NameEntity } from '@global-types/entities/entity-name.entity';

        @Injectable()
        export class FormEntityNameElasticSearchRepository
        implements
        Exact<
            FormEntityNameElasticSearchRepository,
            FormEntityNameRepositoryContract
        > {
        private elasticClient: Client;
        private readonly FORM_ANSWERS_INDEX = 'form_entity-names';
        private readonly FORM_VERSIONS_INDEX = 'form_versions';
        private readonly FORMS_INDEX = 'forms';

        constructor() {
            this.elasticClient = new Client({
            node: process.env.ELASTIC_SEARCH_URL,
            maxRetries: 3,
            requestTimeout: 60000,
            });
        }

        async insertEntityName(
            entity-name: Omit<IEntityName2NameEntity, 'id' | 'date'>,
        ) {
            const document = {
            responses: entity-name.responses,
            formId: entity-name.formId,
            formVersion: entity-name.formVersion,
            date: new Date().toISOString(),
            };

            const result = await this.elasticClient.index({
            index: this.FORM_ANSWERS_INDEX,
            document,
            refresh: true,
            });

            return {
            id: result._id,
            ...document,
            };
        }

        async deleteEntityName(id: string) {
            await this.elasticClient.delete({
            index: this.FORM_ANSWERS_INDEX,
            id,
            refresh: true,
            });

            return { success: true, id };
        }

        async getEntityNameById(id: string) {
            try {
            const response =
                await this.elasticClient.get<IEntityName2NameEntity>({
                index: this.FORM_ANSWERS_INDEX,
                id,
                });

            const entity-name = response._source;
            if (!entity-name) {
                throw new Error(`EntityName with ID ${id} not found`);
            }
            let form: IEntityName2 = null;

            try {
                const versionQuery: estypes.QueryDslQueryContainer =
                {
                bool: {
                    must: [
                    {
                        term: { originalFormId: entity-name.formId },
                    },
                    { term: { version: entity-name.formVersion } },
                    ],
                },
                };

                const { hits: versionHits } =
                await this.elasticClient.search<
                    IEntityName2 & {
                    version: number;
                    originalFormId: string;
                    }
                >({
                    index: this.FORM_VERSIONS_INDEX,
                    query: versionQuery,
                    size: 1,
                });

                if (versionHits.hits.length > 0) {
                const versionHit = versionHits.hits[0];
                form = {
                    id: entity-name.formId,
                    name: versionHit._source.name,
                    elements: versionHit._source.elements,
                    version: versionHit._source.version,
                    date: versionHit._source.date
                    ? new Date(
                        versionHit._source.date,
                    ).toISOString()
                    : null,
                };
                } else {
                // If not found in versions, try the main forms index
                const formQuery: estypes.QueryDslQueryContainer =
                {
                    term: { _id: entity-name.formId },
                };

                const { hits: formHits } =
                    await this.elasticClient.search<IEntityName2>({
                    index: this.FORMS_INDEX, // Make sure this is your main forms index name
                    query: formQuery,
                    size: 1,
                    });

                if (formHits.hits.length > 0) {
                    const formHit = formHits.hits[0];
                    // Check if the form version matches what we need
                    if (
                    formHit._source.version ===
                    entity-name.formVersion
                    ) {
                    form = {
                        id: formHit._id,
                        name: formHit._source.name,
                        elements: formHit._source.elements,
                        version: formHit._source.version,
                        date: formHit._source.date
                        ? new Date(
                            formHit._source.date,
                        ).toISOString()
                        : null,
                    };
                    }
                }
                }
            } catch (error) {
                console.error(
                'Error retrieving form data:',
                error,
                );
            }
            return {
                id: response._id,
                ...response._source,
                form,
            };
            } catch (error) {
            if (error.meta?.statusCode === 404) {
                throw new Error(`EntityName with ID ${id} not found`);
            }
            throw error;
            }
        }
        async getEntityNames({
            search,
            formId,
            page = 1,
            pageSize = 10,
            order = 'date-desc',
        }: GetEntityNamesParams): Promise<GetEntityNamesResponse> {
            const must: estypes.QueryDslQueryContainer[] = [];

            // Add search condition if provided
            if (search) {
            must.push({
                wildcard: { 'responses.*': `*${search}*` },
            });
            }

            // Add formId condition if provided
            if (formId) {
            must.push({
                term: { formId },
            });
            }

            const query: estypes.QueryDslQueryContainer = {
            bool: {
                must: must.length > 0 ? must : [{ match_all: {} }],
            },
            };

            // Count total entity-names matching the query
            const countResult = await this.elasticClient.count({
            index: this.FORM_ANSWERS_INDEX,
            query,
            });

            const total = countResult.count;
            const lastPage = Math.ceil(total / pageSize);
            const hasNextPage = page * pageSize < total;
            const hasPreviousPage = page > 1;

            const { hits } =
            await this.elasticClient.search<IEntityName2NameEntity>({
                index: this.FORM_ANSWERS_INDEX,
                query,
                sort: this.getSort(order),
                from: (page - 1) * pageSize,
                size: pageSize,
            });

            const entity-namesWithForms = await Promise.all(
            hits.hits.map(async (hit) => {
                const entity-name = {
                id: hit._id,
                ...hit._source,
                };

                // First try to find the exact version in the versions index
                let form: IEntityName2 = null;

                try {
                // Try specific version in FORM_VERSIONS_INDEX
                const versionQuery: estypes.QueryDslQueryContainer =
                {
                    bool: {
                    must: [
                        {
                        term: { originalFormId: entity-name.formId },
                        },
                        { term: { version: entity-name.formVersion } },
                    ],
                    },
                };

                const { hits: versionHits } =
                    await this.elasticClient.search<
                    IEntityName2 & {
                        version: number;
                        originalFormId: string;
                    }
                    >({
                    index: this.FORM_VERSIONS_INDEX,
                    query: versionQuery,
                    size: 1,
                    });

                if (versionHits.hits.length > 0) {
                    const versionHit = versionHits.hits[0];
                    form = {
                    id: entity-name.formId,
                    name: versionHit._source.name,
                    elements: versionHit._source.elements,
                    version: versionHit._source.version,
                    date: versionHit._source.date
                        ? new Date(
                        versionHit._source.date,
                        ).toISOString()
                        : null,
                    };
                } else {
                    // If not found in versions, try the main forms index
                    const formQuery: estypes.QueryDslQueryContainer =
                    {
                    term: { _id: entity-name.formId },
                    };

                    const { hits: formHits } =
                    await this.elasticClient.search<IEntityName2>({
                        index: this.FORMS_INDEX, // Make sure this is your main forms index name
                        query: formQuery,
                        size: 1,
                    });

                    if (formHits.hits.length > 0) {
                    const formHit = formHits.hits[0];
                    // Check if the form version matches what we need
                    if (
                        formHit._source.version ===
                        entity-name.formVersion
                    ) {
                        form = {
                        id: formHit._id,
                        name: formHit._source.name,
                        elements: formHit._source.elements,
                        version: formHit._source.version,
                        date: formHit._source.date
                            ? new Date(
                            formHit._source.date,
                            ).toISOString()
                            : null,
                        };
                    }
                    }
                }
                } catch (error) {
                console.error(
                    'Error retrieving form data:',
                    error,
                );
                }

                return {
                ...entity-name,
                form,
                };
            }),
            );

            return {
            data: entity-namesWithForms,
            metadata: {
                hasNextPage,
                hasPreviousPage,
                lastPage,
                total,
                page,
            },
            };
        }
        async getEntityNamesByFormId(
            formId: string,
            {
            page = 1,
            pageSize = 10,
            }: {
            page?: number;
            pageSize?: number;
            } = {},
        ) {
            const query: estypes.QueryDslQueryContainer = {
            bool: {
                must: [{ term: { formId } }],
            },
            };

            const countResult = await this.elasticClient.count({
            index: this.FORM_ANSWERS_INDEX,
            query,
            });

            const total = countResult.count;
            const lastPage = Math.ceil(total / pageSize);
            const hasNextPage = page * pageSize < total;
            const hasPreviousPage = page > 1;

            const { hits } =
            await this.elasticClient.search<IEntityName2NameEntity>({
                index: this.FORM_ANSWERS_INDEX,
                query,
                sort: [{ date: { order: 'desc' } }],
                from: (page - 1) * pageSize,
                size: pageSize,
            });

            return {
            data: hits.hits.map((hit) => ({
                ...hit._source,
                id: hit._id,
            })),
            metadata: {
                hasNextPage,
                hasPreviousPage,
                lastPage,
                total,
                page,
            },
            };
        }

        async getEntityNamesByFormVersion(
            formId: string,
            formVersion: number,
            {
            page = 1,
            pageSize = 10,
            }: {
            page?: number;
            pageSize?: number;
            } = {},
        ) {
            const query: estypes.QueryDslQueryContainer = {
            bool: {
                must: [
                { term: { formId } },
                { term: { formVersion } },
                ],
            },
            };

            const countResult = await this.elasticClient.count({
            index: this.FORM_ANSWERS_INDEX,
            query,
            });

            const total = countResult.count;
            const lastPage = Math.ceil(total / pageSize);
            const hasNextPage = page * pageSize < total;
            const hasPreviousPage = page > 1;

            const { hits } =
            await this.elasticClient.search<IEntityName2NameEntity>({
                index: this.FORM_ANSWERS_INDEX,
                query,
                sort: [{ date: { order: 'desc' } }],
                from: (page - 1) * pageSize,
                size: pageSize,
            });

            return {
            data: hits.hits.map((hit) => ({
                ...hit._source,
                id: hit._id,
            })),
            metadata: {
                hasNextPage,
                hasPreviousPage,
                lastPage,
                total,
                page,
            },
            };
        }
        private getSort(order: OrderEntityName): any[] {
            switch (order) {
            case 'date-asc':
                return [{ date: { order: 'asc' } }];
            case 'date-desc':
                return [{ date: { order: 'desc' } }];
            default:
                return [{ date: { order: 'desc' } }];
            }
        }
        }


    ```

9. How implement Contract Repository in service
   - First you need check if has one repository token in 
   backend/src/infra/database/tokens/repository-tokens.ts
   this token is like :
   ``` typescript
   export const REPOSITORY_TOKENS = {
        ENTITY_NAME_REPOSITORY: Symbol('IEntityNameRepository'),
   }
    ```

    and in backend/src/infra/database/database.providers.ts

    - need has this 

    ```typescript
       export const repositoryProviders: Provider[] [ {
       EntityNamePrismaRepository,
        {
            provide: REPOSITORY_TOKENS.ENTITY_NAME_REPOSITORY,
            useClass: EntityNamePrismaRepository,
        },
        }
        ]
    ```

   - To implement the contractRepository you need inject the contract in /backend/src/modules/module-name/services/entity-name.service.ts
   - Example of class service Inject contract:
    ```typescript
    
    import { REPOSITORY_TOKENS } from 'src/infra/database/tokens/repository-tokens';
    import { IEntityNameContractRepository } from "../repositories/entity-name/entity-name.contract.repository.ts";
    
    @Injectable({ scope: Scope.TRANSIENT })
    export class EntityNameService {
        constructor(
            @Inject(REPOSITORY_TOKENS.ENTITY_NAME_REPOSITORY)
            private readonly entityNameRepository: IEntityNameContractRepository,
        ) { }
    }

    ```
    

10. How implement Prisma Repository in module
   - To implement the contractRepository you DONT need inject the contract in /apps/backend/src/modules/module-name/entity-name.module.ts because already is injected in backend/src/infra/database/database.providers.ts
   - Example of class service Inject contract:
    ```typescript
    @Module({
        imports: [],
        controllers: [],
        providers: [
          
        ],
        exports: [],
    })
    export class EntityName {}


    ```
    
11. Validation checklist:
   - All required fields are properly typed
   - No unnecessary fields are included in body requests
   - Proper use of optional fields with `?` notation
   - Consistent use of enums and custom types
   - Proper nesting of related types
   - In module and service need have same name of entitie

This rule helps maintain consistency between entity definitions and API payloads, reducing runtime errors and improving type safety.